commits.message: Fixed copyright info in license file

Fixed timezone directive handling

Fixed a typo that were preventing %z directives from being correctly recognized, and the parser should no longer mistake strings like %m-%Y for %m%z.
Copied detect_format docstring from DSoptions method to __init__'s magic function

So I heard you like readme edits

Clearer rule definition example

Quick readme edit

Made example code accurate as of previous commit

Added more magic

Users can now type "DateSense.detect_format" instead of "DateSense.DSoptions.detect_format".
Added the sorts of things to __init__.py that belong in __init__.py

Better pattern rule handling

Added minmatchscore argument to pattern rule constructor. Also upated some out-of-date documentation.

Better rule constructors

Reordered arguments and made some optional for DSrule class constructors

More readme changes

Made code example more example-y

Changes to readme

Fixed some typos, misplaced words, etc.
